#-#-# AI Koans, Sussman attains enlightenment #-#-#
  In the days when Sussman was a novice, Minsky once came to
  him as he sat hacking at the PDP-6. “What are you doing?”,
  asked Minsky. “I am training a randomly wired neural net to
  play Tic-Tac-Toe” Sussman replied. “Why is the net wired randomly?”,
  asked Minsky. “I do not want it to have any preconceptions of how
  to play”, Sussman said. Minsky then shut his eyes. “Why do you
  close your eyes?”, Sussman asked his teacher. “So that the
  room will be empty.” At that moment, Sussman was enlightened.

#-#-# Edwin Pickman, Monstrous Eye #-#-#
  I have seen the moon, awful and pale As looking upon me,
  In its darkened sail. No blinks , no closing just stared
  too hot, Like the eye of a monstrous god! How dare ye own
  the sun's own beams. Without them ye're naught, all pass ye
  by. Don't look upon me ye monstrous eye! 'Cause when the sun
  comes, ye'll disappear like dreams! Pale, lifeless, malicious
  sentry of night, Shouted out, so that the clouds all flee
  from sight, And the raging winds suddenly died out to hear
  what the unblinking eye will say to make me fear. But it
  has done nothing yet still staring at me. Monstrous eye
  perceive! I to am just like thee!

#-#-# Edwin Pickman, Lurkers' Call #-#-#
  I have seen them all,
  Through insanity's omnipresent soul,
  As burning, turning and blasphemously
  churning,
  Smiling, mocking and heinously laughing
  While carrying winds did haul
  Aside, to everlasting, eternal spheres,
  Dim, bleak and heretically foul.
  Now, from a distance seem indefinitely tall,
  Sinisterly lurk, wait and in silence they
  crawl.
  And from a lightless, strangely carved
  basaltic hall
  Insistently they bawl, howl and call...

#-#-# Edwin Pickman, A Dream #-#-#
  Beyond the clouds of consciousnesses, I dream a
  purple haze, From windy heights, down to my poorly
  self, it leaks in to the maze, Of my soul, my burden
  - too heavy now to lift - my binding dreary lace, And
  strikes me, shrieks, hisses, but yet tenderly kisses me
  in my cursed state of daze!
  A haze, so bright, and brighter yet then sun's ever burning
  face, Yet cold, calm and so softly falling, as the blue
  light of the moon that sets, My demon, my soul - now
  An ill, shaded wraith - once my brightly glowing
  grace, Now I look, quietly with a mourning face, and
  as if, I'm drifting, towards death I pace...

