#-#-# Seneca 4 BC – AD 65, Seneca's Minor Dialogues #-#-#
  Death is the release from all pain and complete cessation, beyond
  which our suffering will not extend. It will return us to that
  condition of tranquility, which we had enjoyed before we were born.
  Should anyone mourn the deceased, then he must also mourn the unborn.
  Death is neither good nor evil, for good or evil can only be something
  that actually exists. However, whatever is of itself nothing and
  which transforms everything else into nothing will
  not all be able to put us at the mercy of Fate.

